<plot>World Cup, summer of 2002. Make-or-break. Korea against Italy and two nations crossing their fingers. But not only on the football turf a final battle is carried out. The Italian mafia against the Korean mafia. A game with fixed rules and an ending that is always fatal. And right in the middle of it are Si-Yeon and Finn, inevitably connected by their fate. Actually, I already won, thinks Finn - just a simple money transfer, but then everything goes wrong. The son of the Korean mafia leader is dead, and Finn is blamed for his death. They want him to pay with his life. But Si-Yeon play her own game. Korea and Italy are storming off and Si-Yeon and Finn have these 90 minutes left to get their revenge and 90 minutes for Finn to find a way to survive. Two opponents are forced to play in order to win.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?194875</url></doc>
